JOHANNESBURG - The Department of Basic Education (DBE) has announced that the results for the 2017 matric exams will be released by the Minister of Education on 4 January 2018 and pupils will be able to collect their results at schools and examination centres on 5 January 2018.  The matric exams drew to a close on Tuesday and according to the DBE, a total of 802 636 candidates, 634 527 of those who are full-time pupils, sat for the examination that began on 16 October.  READ: Matric examinations running smoothly: DBE ‘’The 2017 National Senior Certificate (NSC) examinations have been free of any major incident and the Department would like to thank those learners and the commitment of teachers who worked tirelessly throughout the year to ensure that candidates were prepared and that the integrity of the NSC examinations continues to be upheld,’’ said Basic Education Minister, Angie Motshekga. According to the DBE, the task of marking millions of examination scripts has already begun in Gauteng and Limpopo. The remaining provinces are due to commence on Wednesday. There are 44 911 markers and 144 marking centers across the country checking more than 10 million answer sheets. eNCA